The paper introduces a new format for fast computation of a product of many potentials, which is a key operation in the junction tree algorithm used in probabilistic graphical models. This suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to sub-categories related to probabilistic graphical models, such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), data mining (cs.DM), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
